<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.automation.apple-events</key>
    <true/>
    <!--
      Issue #845: data-protection keychain access for OpenAI/Gemini API key
      storage. Non-sandboxed Developer-ID-signed macOS apps need an explicit
      keychain-access-groups entitlement to use SecItem* with
      kSecUseDataProtectionKeychain: true (Apple TN3137). Sandboxed apps get
      the equivalent application-identifier auto-derived; we don't, so we
      declare it. The "9UT54V24XG" prefix is the EnviousLabs team ID, present
      on both "Developer ID Application: Saurabh Vaish (9UT54V24XG)" and
      "Developer ID Application: ENVIOUS LABS LLC (9UT54V24XG)" certs used by
      the release pipeline. The first entry is the default access group used
      by SecItemAdd when no explicit kSecAttrAccessGroup is set.

      Issue #913: keychain-access-groups is a RESTRICTED entitlement that AMFI
      requires to be authorized by an embedded Developer ID provisioning profile
      at launch (Apple TN3125). Without it the notarized release app fails to
      spawn on macOS 26 (taskgated "no eligible provisioning profiles found" ->
      amfid -413 -> runningboardd error=163). scripts/build-dmg.sh embeds
      signing/EnviousWispr_DeveloperID.provisionprofile at
      Contents/embedded.provisionprofile before the final codesign; that profile
      carries keychain-access-groups ['9UT54V24XG.*'] which authorizes the group
      below. The application-identifier + team-identifier keys below MUST match
      the profile (and the Release bundle id) for the profile to validate. The
      DEV build omits all three (EnviousWispr-Dev.entitlements) — self-signed,
      file-based key storage, no profile.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.application-identifier</key>
    <string>9UT54V24XG.com.enviouswispr.app</string>
    <key>com.apple.developer.team-identifier</key>
    <string>9UT54V24XG</string>
    <key>keychain-access-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>9UT54V24XG.com.enviouswispr.app</string>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
